---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MiniGrowthCalc from '../components/calculators/MiniGrowthCalc';
import { breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema } from '../lib/seo/schema';

const siteUrl = 'https://trumpaccounts.guide';

const schemas = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: siteUrl },
    { name: 'Birthday Gifts That Grow', url: `${siteUrl}/birthday` },
  ]),
  faqSchema([
    {
      question: 'Can I contribute to a child\'s Trump Account as a birthday gift?',
      answer: 'Yes! Anyone can contribute to a child\'s Trump Account. You can give cash or check to the parents to deposit, or contribute directly through trumpaccounts.gov. Contributions are after-tax and count toward the $5,000 annual limit.',
    },
    {
      question: 'How much should I contribute to a Trump Account as a birthday gift?',
      answer: 'Any amount helps. Even a $25 birthday gift invested in an S&P 500 index fund can grow significantly over time thanks to compound interest. For context, $50 invested at birth could be worth over $200 by age 18 and over $7,000 by retirement.',
    },
    {
      question: 'What is a Trump Account?',
      answer: 'A Trump Account is a tax-advantaged investment account created by the One Big Beautiful Bill Act (IRC ¬ß530A). Children born 2025-2028 receive a $1,000 federal pilot deposit. The money is invested in S&P 500 index funds until age 18, when it converts to a traditional IRA.',
    },
  ]),
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Give a Birthday Gift That Grows ‚Äî Trump Account Contributions"
  description="Instead of another toy, contribute to a child's Trump Account. A $50 birthday gift could grow to $200+ by age 18. Learn how birthday contributions work."
  schema={schemas}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 text-center md:py-24">
      <p class="text-4xl">üéÅ</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold text-white md:text-5xl">
        Someone Wants to Invest<br />in a Child's Future
      </h1>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-gray-400">
        You received a card asking you to contribute to a child's <strong class="text-white">Trump Account</strong>
        instead of buying a toy. Here's why that's a brilliant idea ‚Äî and how you can do the same for your kids.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Math -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700 bg-surface-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white">Why Birthday Contributions Beat Toys</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-2xl text-center text-gray-400">
        Toys break. Compound interest doesn't.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-900 p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">$50 gift at age 1</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold text-gold-400">$185</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">by age 18</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-900 p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">$50 gift at age 5</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold text-gold-400">$136</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">by age 18</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-900 p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">$100 gift at birth</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold text-gold-400">$400</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">by age 18</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-center text-xs text-gray-500">
        Assumes 8% average annual return (historical S&P 500 average). Not financial advice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Is a Trump Account? -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white">What Is a Trump Account?</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800 p-5">
          <p class="font-bold text-gold-400">$1,000 Free</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            Children born 2025‚Äì2028 get a federal pilot deposit of $1,000, invested automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800 p-5">
          <p class="font-bold text-gold-400">$5,000/yr Limit</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            Parents, grandparents, and anyone can contribute up to $5,000 per year (after-tax).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800 p-5">
          <p class="font-bold text-gold-400">S&P 500 Invested</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            Money goes into S&P 500 or broad U.S. equity index funds ‚Äî the same funds billionaires use.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800 p-5">
          <p class="font-bold text-gold-400">IRA at 18</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            At age 18, it converts to a traditional IRA. The child owns it for life.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 text-center">
        <a href="/what-are-trump-accounts" class="text-sm font-medium text-gold-400 no-underline hover:text-gold-300">
          Read the complete guide &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Growth Calculator -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700 bg-surface-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white">See How Birthday Gifts Grow</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-2 max-w-md text-center text-sm text-gray-400">
        Enter a monthly contribution to see projected growth. All calculations run in your browser ‚Äî no data collected.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-surface-600 bg-surface-900 p-6">
        <MiniGrowthCalc client:visible />
        <a href="/calculators/growth-calculator" class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm font-medium text-gold-400 no-underline hover:text-gold-300">
          Full calculator with charts &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Create Your Own Card ‚Äî THE VIRAL LOOP -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 text-center">
      <p class="text-5xl">üéÇ</p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-bold text-white md:text-3xl">
        Want One for <em>Your</em> Child's Birthday?
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-lg text-gray-400">
        Create a free birthday contribution card in 30 seconds. Share it in your party group chat
        and let every guest know how to invest in your child's future.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/tools/birthday-card"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-gold-500 px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-surface-900 no-underline transition-colors hover:bg-gold-400"
      >
        Create Your Birthday Card
        <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
        </svg>
      </a>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
        Free forever. No signup. No data collected.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Contribute -->
  <section class="border-b border-surface-700 bg-surface-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white">How to Contribute as a Guest</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-gold-400/15 text-gold-400">
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 font-bold text-white">Get Details</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            Ask the parents for their Trump Account details or if they prefer cash/check.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-gold-400/15 text-gold-400">
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 font-bold text-white">Contribute</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            Give directly via trumpaccounts.gov, or hand cash/check to the parents to deposit.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-gold-400/15 text-gold-400">
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 font-bold text-white">Watch It Grow</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">
            The money is invested in S&P 500 funds and grows tax-deferred until age 18.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-white">Can anyone contribute to a child's Trump Account?</summary>
          <div class="border-t border-surface-700 px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-300">
            Yes. Parents, grandparents, aunts, uncles, family friends ‚Äî anyone can contribute. All contributions count toward the $5,000 annual limit. Contributions are after-tax (no tax deduction for the giver).
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-white">How much should I give as a birthday contribution?</summary>
          <div class="border-t border-surface-700 px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-300">
            Any amount is meaningful! Even $25 grows significantly over 18 years of compound interest. A common approach: give the same amount you'd spend on a toy ($25-$100) but put it into their Trump Account instead. The child won't remember the toy, but they'll thank you at 18.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-white">Does my child need a Trump Account already open?</summary>
          <div class="border-t border-surface-700 px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-300">
            You'll need to file IRS Form 4547 to elect a Trump Account. This can be done with your 2025 tax return (due April 15, 2026) or through the trumpaccounts.gov portal starting mid-2026. Once the account is active, anyone can contribute.
            <a href="/how-to-open-trump-account" class="mt-2 block font-medium text-gold-400 no-underline">How to open a Trump Account &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group rounded-lg border border-surface-600 bg-surface-800">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-white">Is a Trump Account better than a 529 plan?</summary>
          <div class="border-t border-surface-700 px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-300">
            They're different tools. A 529 is specifically for education expenses (tax-free withdrawals for qualified education). A Trump Account converts to a traditional IRA at 18 and can be used for anything ‚Äî retirement, a home, emergencies. Most financial advisors recommend using both.
            <a href="/compare" class="mt-2 block font-medium text-gold-400 no-underline">Full comparison: Trump Account vs 529 &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
